results.description:
White Rock lake, Winfrey Point
A cute little native bee was busy feeding and pollinating a Queen Anne's lace wildflower.  Preserving prairie lands is also helping to bring back the native bee & wasp population, which is important for crop fertilization.  A male.
Id confirmed on bugguide by John Ascher here:  https://bugguide.net/node/view/1472513
@johnascher
